summary:
"I'm not a squirrel," she said. 

“I’ll almost be a woman soon. I’ll be one-and-ten.”

  tbh i love arya asserting her girlhood...
body:
“I’m not a squirrel,” she said. “I’ll almost be a woman soon. I’ll be one-and-ten.”

tbh i love arya asserting her girlhood here. she’s had it violently taken from her and had to live as a boy for survival (and she was always treated by society as being a “bad” kind of girl) but despite that arya sees herself growing into a woman.

summary: my s8 predictions there won’t be iron throne at the end! a Stark will rule over the seven kingdoms (my money is on Sansa), but...
body:
my s8 predictions

there won’t be iron throne at the end!

a Stark will rule over the seven kingdoms (my money is on Sansa), but i’m also not sure that westeros will be under one ruler only, soo

Daenerys, dies as a hero, becomes a villain (later dies) or returns to Essos (she won’t rule in westeros)

Cersei will die but first she will see Sansa turn into the younger more beautiful queen, the better version of herself

Arya will be the master of arms or/and she becomes a queen (Gendy, might as well be named king of the seven kingdoms, and well they HAVE to be endgame)

Varys or Tyrion will be the ones to help either Sansa or Gendry to be the new rulers 

Jon, as much as I want him to live, my hopes are very little (in my heart i want him to have a happily ever after with Sansa but this is GoT, they don’t do disney endings so we won’t get that) 

Jaime will die serving one of the Starks, he will finally be honorable in the eyes of the realm 

Bran dies, sadly, he’s an important character against the night king

Davos will be hand of the king/queen

contenders to be named king/queen of one (or the seven) kingdoms:

Sansa Stark, Arya Stark, Gendry, Yara Greyjoy

people i think will survive:

Arya Stark, Sansa Stark, Gendry, Davos, Brienne, Missandei, Tyrion, Yara, Sam, Gilly, Tormund, Lyanna

people i think will die:

Jon Snow, Bran, Varys, Cersei, Daenerys, Jaime, Jorah, Euron

title: arya vs. sansa, nah!
body:
so as many of us the 3s of GoT put my mind to work, and since Sansa haters are so convinced that Sansa will betray the Starks, here’s my theory…

Sansa will be cold to Dany, she won’t be as one of her followers, she believes in the northern independence  and she will question Jon and will put the dragon queen in her place but here the twist, Arya will be proud of her, finally her sister fights for her family and their land, she won’t be pissed as many haters are expecting

the pack survives!
